Hello Everyone !!

Welcome to Zine Orientation 2023. I hope you're having a great time and are not fast asleep. This announcement channel would be updated with all the latest news from us. 

Team Zine

Hey Freshers !

We are all ready and excited for the upcoming recruitment and workshop that we have planned for you, so we hope ypu all have registered for the same.

This announcement channel will be used to communicate important details and updates about the workshop, so ask your friends to install the app too.

Team Zine

Hey everyone!

We'll see you tomorrow at the computer center for the Aptitude Test at 10:00 AM, to get your gears going. After which the first workshop topic will be held right after the test is completed, i.e, BME (Basic Mechanical Engineering). There'll be a hands-on with the knowledge you gain from the topics taught and would be your first bot, so try not to miss the fun !

Set your alarms and we'll see you there ! 

Team Zine
We'll take exam of Section-E enrolled students who have extra classes at 11.15 AM

Materials required for tomorrow's Aptitude Test - 

- A pen
- A copy or paper for rough work
- A well fed stomach &
- Your fresh brain
Please report at CC - LAB 1 for the Aptitude Test
The first workshop, i.e, BME (Basic Mechanical Engineering) will be conducted in VLTC-007.
The second workshop, BEE (Basic Electrical Engineering) along with Hands on will be conducted in VLTC-007 at 3:00 PM
The box dimension for the hands on is 7cm +_ 10%

Tomorrow's Algorithm and Introduction to Machine Learning session will start at 10:00AM at VLTC-007.

Kindly carry your laptops with you for this session for the Hands on. 
Set your alarms and get ready to dive into the world of code.

See you there !

Todays Cyber Security session will start at 6PM at LT-02 in Electrical Department

Kindly carry your laptops with you for this sessions hands on.

See you there !
LT-2 is at the entrance of dept of Metallurgy and materials research North Gate (the entrance b/w canteen and the way towards library)

Tomorrow's IC/MCUs session will start at 10:00 AM at VLTC-007. This session is the most exciting as we will be diving into the world of microcontrollers and then we will program them to achieve some basic tasks.

Carry your laptops for the hands on session (programming the microcontrollers)

This is one of the best and most important workshops, do not miss it !

See you there !

New update for the app is available on Play Store.

*Update Notes*
- Chat UI fixes
- Now you can copy paste links or messages from the chats

Today's Sensors(IC/MCU part 2) session will start at 3:00 PM at VLTC-007.There will be a fun hands on session where teams will be provided with electric/electronic components,IC's and sensors and they have to build their circuits to achieve a common task.This is will also be the last workshop of the series and will have a small interaction session towards the end.See you guys over there !

Guys please fill a feedback form , it is compulsory for everyone . It helps us change , update our content and the flow of our workshops.

https://forms.gle/gWJeoZy2pHCYSLPQ8

Fasten your seatbelts as in Stage 3 we dive into building an entire project from scratch in a 5 days using concepts learned in the workshop. You will be given an opportunity to choose a project in a particular domain of liking from a list of projects, once chosen you will be assigned a mentor, with whom you will coordinate and build on your project. 

Do not be afraid to try and learn something new!!

The shortlisted candidates from Stage 2 and projects list will be released by tonight and further instructions will be given.

Congratulations to everyone who has made it to stage 3 ! if helicopter and drone require torque balancing but why it is not required in aeroplanes
boss Monday evening ke workshop Tuesday morning me rakh lo, evening me time nahi milega

helicopters and drone require torque balancing, because of the unwanted torque generated by the rotating blades along the axis of the aircraft, whereas in aeroplanes the propeller rotates in axis perpendicular to the aircraft, hence no such torque is produced which can  affect the aircraft and hence torque balancing is not required.
